ğŸ§  CORE INTERVIEW INSIGHT (VERY IMPORTANT)

ğŸ’¡ Rotation can be done in TWO SIMPLE STEPS

STEP 1ï¸âƒ£: Transpose the matrix

ğŸ‘‰ Convert rows â†’ columns

STEP 2ï¸âƒ£: Reverse each row

Thatâ€™s it ğŸ”¥
This avoids extra space and works in-place.

ğŸ› ï¸ STEP-BY-STEP ALGORITHM
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Transpose

Swap:

matrix[i][j] â†” matrix[j][i]


Only swap upper triangle to avoid double swapping.

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Reverse each row

For every row:

reverse(row)

â±ï¸ COMPLEXITY
Metric	Value
Time	O(nÂ²)
Space	O(1) (in-place)
ğŸ’» JAVA CODE (INTERVIEW-PERFECT)
class Solution {
    public void rotate(int[][] matrix) {

        int n = matrix.length;

        // STEP 1: Transpose the matrix
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {

                int temp = matrix[i][j];
                matrix[i][j] = matrix[j][i];
                matrix[j][i] = temp;
            }
        }

        // STEP 2: Reverse each row
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {

            int left = 0;
            int right = n - 1;

            while (left < right) {
                int temp = matrix[i][left];
                matrix[i][left] = matrix[i][right];
                matrix[i][right] = temp;

                left++;
                right--;
            }
        }
    }
}

ğŸ§¾ LINE-BY-LINE EXPLANATION (VERY CLEAR)
ğŸ”¹ Transpose logic
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    for (int j = i; j < n; j++) {


â¡ï¸ j = i avoids double swapping

int temp = matrix[i][j];
matrix[i][j] = matrix[j][i];
matrix[j][i] = temp;


â¡ï¸ Swaps row â†” column elements

ğŸ”¹ Reverse row logic
int left = 0;
int right = n - 1;


â¡ï¸ Two-pointer technique

while (left < right)


â¡ï¸ Reverse row like an array

left++;
right--;


â¡ï¸ Move pointers inward

